Examples
       The  following  command specifies that stripes that jog to connect to a
       target always use the stripe width.

       setAddStripeMode -use_stripe_width 1

       The following examples include commands for specifying that stripes are
       generated in the block with a specified orthogonal offset:

       setAddStripeMode -orthogonal_offset {{1 9 11 13 orthogonal_offset1}  {2
       orthogonal_offset2}  {3  orthogonal_offset3}  {5 orthogonal_offset5} {7
       orthogonal_offset7} {8 orthogonal_offset8}}

       addStripe -layer green ...

       addStripe -layer blue ...

       setAddStripeMode -orthogonal_offset {{1 orthogonal_offset1} {3 orthogo-
       nal_offset3} {7 orthogonal_offset7} {11 orthogonal_offset11}}

       addStripe -layer red ...

       setAddStripeMode -orthogonal_offset {{3 7 orthogonal_offset3} {1 5 9 11
       13 orthogonal1}}

       addStripe -layer blue ...

